| Command | Function |
| ------------------------------------ | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| /deposit <amount> | Member requests deposit of tokens into the vault. The bot creates a transaction sending the amount to the Safe. Once the transaction is executed (with required signatures), the member’s share is recorded in the database. |
| /balance | Shows the member’s share and the total DAO treasury. |
| /propose_trade asset1->asset2 amount | A Trader proposes a trade. The bot creates a Snapshot proposal with details (asset, amount, expected price, reason). |
| /vote <proposal_id> yes/no | Member signs an off‑chain vote via Snapshot. |
| /execute <proposal_id> | After the proposal passes, the bot uses the Safe Governor module to execute the trade via the DEX aggregator. |
| /assign_trader @user | Admin proposes to assign a trader hat to a Telegram user. This triggers a Snapshot vote. If passed, Hats Protocol updates the Safe multisig signers. |
| /leave | Member exits and withdraws their share (minus gas and slippage), triggering a multisig transaction. |
  
  
**UX**: Each command should produce clear instructions and confirm actions. Sensitive operations (withdraw, trade execution) require confirmations and, ideally, 2FA (e.g., time‑based one‑time password or hardware wallet). The bot should support inline buttons and interactive menus for non‑command users.  
  
